benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/customFields - Add custom fields to payment

covered: POST Valid Payload: Happy path covered by TC01 (and reinforced by TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05 with valid payloads).
POST Invalid Payload: Malformed JSON covered by TC08.
POST Invalid Payload: Missing required fields covered by TC16.
POST Large Payloads: Large payload handling covered by TC15.
Validation Coverage: Field-level validation, extra/missing fields covered by TC01, TC06, TC16.
Authorization Coverage: Missing header and invalid token scenarios covered by TC09 and TC12.
Server/Error Handling: Service unavailability covered by TC13 (503).
Security: Handling of SQL injection/XSS payloads covered by TC14.
Performance: Normal and peak load scenarios covered by TC22 and TC23.
Concurrency: Concurrent requests covered by TC19.
Persistence/Integration: Data persistence verified by TC24 and data consistency across systems by TC25.
Unicode Handling: Unicode in fieldValue covered by TC21.
Timeout/Network: Network latency scenario covered by TC18.
Edge/Input Scenarios: Empty body (TC07) and unexpected parameters (TC17) covered.
gaps: Duplicate Submission: No explicit test for idempotent duplicate submissions of the same payload.
500 Internal Server Error: No test simulates a server-side 500 error on failure.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control).
recommendations: Add a test for idempotent duplicate submissions to verify handling of repeated payloads.
Add a test simulating server-side failures to validate 500 Internal Server Error handling.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to assess behavior under high request volume.
Add tests for caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control headers) to validate client-side caching semantics.
Consider adding explicit 403 Forbidden tests for permission-related access control if applicable.
